Gunmen suspected to be Fulani herdsmen on Sunday night invaded Kukum Daji village in Kaura Local Government Area of Kaduna State, killing more than twenty residents of the area. Also, the Southern Kaduna Peoples Union while condemning the fresh attack on Kukum Daji, alleged that five persons including children were also killed on Friday, July 17, 2020 by suspected Fulani militia. On the attack on Kukum Daji village, it was gathered that more than 30 persons sustained injuries. According to an eyewitness, 17 persons, mostly youth that attended a wedding party, died on the spot while three persons were later confirmed dead. Our correspondent learnt that the attackers, who were heavily armed with rifles and other dangerous weapons, invaded the village, under Kagoro Chiefdom at about 11:00 pm and attacked the residents, mostly youths who were attending a wedding party in the area. Meanwhile, the Kaduna State Police Command has confirmed the attack on Monday. The Police Public Relations Officer in the state, ASP Mohammed Jalige, who confirmed the incident, however, said the command had yet to ascertain the casualty figures. Jalige said security has been beefed up in the village and its environs. “Yes, there was an attack on Kukum Daji Village of Kaura Local Government area yesterday night. “The area has been fortified, but we are yet to confirm the number of casualties. As soon as we get that, I will get back to you,” the police spokesman said. According to an eyewitness, the attackers shot sporadically as they approached the village, adding that aside those killed, some villagers are still missing. The eyewitness said some of those that sustained injuries during the attacks were taken to the Kafanchan General Hospital, where they were currently receiving treatment. Speaking on the incident, the president of the community association, Yashen Titus,  told journalists on Monday the victims were shot dead at an after wedding party in one of the houses in the village.